.TE
.SS "Time Durations"
The various duration parameters to the
.B post
command are formatted as a string of numbers followed by a single-letter code indicating time units,
such as
.RB \*(lq 3m \*(rq
for 3 minutes,
.RB \*(lq 5h \*(rq
for 5 hours,
and
.RB \*(lq 1d,10h3m42s \*(rq
for 1 day, 10 hours, 3 minutes, and 42 seconds.
.SS "Time and Date"
The time and date parameters to the
.B post
command have the general form
.RS
.RI [ day \f[CR]@\fP][ hour ]\f[CR]:\fP min [\f[CR]:\fP sec ]
.RE
where
.I day
is the name of the day of the week, and the others are decimal integer values
using 24-hour time for the
.I hour
value.
.LP
The parameter may also be a single
.I day
by itself, or it may have the form of a duration in which case it represents that much elapsed time from the current time.
.LP
The
.B visible
parameter to
.B post
is actually a pair of date time values separated by a hyphen
.RB (\*(lq \- \*(rq).
